title: Mount Blackwood
text:
Mount Blackwood is a <a href="mountain">mountain</a> located within the boundaries of the <a href="Mackay%2C%20Queensland">Mackay</a> Regional Council in <a href="Central%20Queensland">Central Queensland</a>, <a href="Australia">Australia</a> and has an elevation of 639m. It is covered in dense tropical rainforest and is home to the <a href="Graptophyllum%20ilicifolium">Mount Blackwood Holly</a> ("<a href="Graptophyllum%20ilicifolium">Graptophyllum ilicifolium</a>"), a species of shrub <a href="endemic">endemic</a> to the area. It also has the <a href="Pioneer%20Valley">Pioneer Valley</a> close to the region. Also nearby mountains are <a href="Mt%20Jukes">Mt Jukes</a>, <a href="Mount%20Ossa%20%28Queensland%29">Mt Ossa</a> and Mt Brampton.
Mount Blackwood is used for commercial <a href="television">television</a> transmission, such as <a href="ABC%20Queensland">ABC Queensland</a>, and other communications in the <a href="Mackay%2C%20Queensland">Mackay</a> district. It is also used for transmission of <a href="VHF">VHF</a> Automatic En Route Information Service (AERIS) broadcasts for civil aviation.
